news.title: PMLA court orders restitution of assets worth Rs 12 crore to depositors in Rose Valley fraud case
news.para: These fixed deposits were attached by the Enforcement Directorate (ED) under the anti-money laundering law some years ago after it booked a case against the Rose Valley Group, its chairman Gautam Kundu and others in 2014.

news.title: Mahindra Lifespaces, Actis form joint venture to build industrial & logistics park in Chennai
news.para: Mahindra Lifespace Developers and Actis formed Ample Parks, a joint venture to develop industrial and logistics parks in India. Their initial 70-acre project in Chennai marks the beginning of a plan to acquire and develop 1.5 million square meters of greenfield and brownfield sites. Actis holds a majority stake, with Mahindra Lifespaces owning a significant minority.

news.title: NCLT approves Rs 184 crore resolution plan for Satra Properties
news.para: The tribunal also set aside the erstwhile promoter’s application that alleged undervaluation of the company’s properties by its resolution professional (RP). The RP had received claims of about Rs 719 crore. Erstwhile promoter Praful Satra had filed an intervention application against the RP, alleging illegality and undervaluation in the resolution plan

news.title: Keystone Realtors' profit down 45 % to Rs 26 crore in Q1 FY25
news.para: Total income increased to Rs 437.20 crore during April-June period of this fiscal from Rs 282.82 crore in the corresponding period of the previous year.

news.title: Parsvnath Developers says matters pertaining to non-bailable warrants against Sanjeev Jain resolved
news.para: "Jain was arrested on Saturday by the STF team of Shahdara from the IGI airport following non-bailable warrants issued against the CEO for his inability to appear before the National Consumer Disputes Redressal Commission," Deputy Commissioner of Police (Shahdara) Surendra Choudhary said in a statement on Sunday.

news.title: Godrej Properties' net debt rises 20% to Rs 7,432 crore in Q1 FY25
news.para: Godrej Properties' total income grew to Rs 1,699.48 crore during the April-June period of 2024-25 fiscal from Rs 1,265.98 crore in the corresponding period of the previous year, according to a regulatory filing.

news.title: SFIO probe into Sahara group companies ongoing: Finance minister
news.para: Union Finance Minister Nirmala Sitharaman informed the Lok Sabha that the Serious Fraud Investigation Office (SFIO) is probing Sahara group companies, with further action pending the report. Despite 3.7 crore investors, only 19,650 have claimed refunds. The Supreme Court is overseeing the process, and the government is acting accordingly.

news.title: Centre proposes to declare 108 Goan villages as ecologically sensitive areas
news.para: In July 2022, the Union ministry issued a draft notification proposing that 99 Goa villages, spread over 1,461sqkm, be declared as ESAs. In June 2024, the Union ministry agreed that there were discrepancies between the plan and the villages that had been included in the draft notification of 99 villages, and it would be rectified.

news.title: Centre planning to restore NCZ in draft regional plan 2041 to protect Aravalis
news.para: The government planned to restore the Natural Conservation Zone (NCZ) in the Regional Plan 2041 for the NCR, which aims to protect areas like the Aravali ridge and major water bodies. The draft will maintain the definition of the Aravali range as designated in a 1992 notification unless directed otherwise by competent authorities or the Supreme Court.

news.title: Chandigarh: Over 15,000 CHB allottees owe Rs 65 crore in outstanding rental dues
news.para: There are several such instances wherein the CHB cancelled the allotment and thereafter initiated the eviction process against rent defaulters, but even after multiple years of efforts it failed to complete the eviction process.

news.title: Karnataka SCDRC orders Mega City (Bengaluru) Developers to pay buyer Rs 7 lakh
news.para: An 81-year-old Bengaluru resident, PP Sharma, succeeded in his legal battle against Mega City Developers for selling him a litigation-prone site. The Karnataka State Consumer Disputes Redressal Commission ordered the firm to refund Rs 4.9 lakh with interest and pay Rs 2 lakh in compensation alongside Rs 25,000 in litigation costs for unfair trade practices.

news.title: Bengaluru development body mulls hike in villa prices in Hunnigere
news.para: The final pricing will be confirmed in the upcoming board meeting. The construction of these villas was completed in June, but allotments have been delayed. The project, which spans 31 acres in Hennur, also includes flats on Tumkur Road.

news.title: No plan to hike property tax this year, BMC informs Maharashtra government
news.para: Every year, property tax is collected by BMC from the over 9 lakh properties over which the municipal corporation has jurisdiction.

news.title: Gurugram: Years of delay & fund diversion probe leave ATS Marigold buyers in a fix
news.para: Homebuyers approached the National Consumer Disputes Redressal Commission/Economic Offences Wing in 2021, seeking a refund of the amount they had paid along with interest.

news.title: GST demand on development rights push landowners into legal dilemma
news.para: The development is causing confusion and concern among landowners, given that the matter of taxability on such transactions is currently pending before the Supreme Court.

news.title: Income tax department examines overseas property investments by Indian residents
news.para: The Income Tax Department is now examining overseas property investments by Indian residents, including recent acquisitions in Switzerland and Portugal.

news.title: Delhi police arrests Parsvnath Landmark Developers' CEO
news.para: ​"Jain was arrested on Saturday by the STF team of Shahdara from the IGI airport following non-bailable warrants issued against the CEO for his inability to appear before the National Consumer Disputes Redressal Commission," Deputy Commissioner of Police (Shahdara) Surendra Choudhary said in a statement.

news.title: Dharavi redevelopment plan gets shot in the arm as resident body supports government survey
news.para: Representatives of Citizen and Society Development Welfare, who have given the slogan of Dharavi Banao Andolan, met Srinivas and submitted a memorandum seeking expedition of the survey being conducted in Dharavi.

news.title: UP-RERA improves the facility for QPR filing of projects
news.para: U.P. RERA has simplified and upgraded the facility for filing of QPR of the projects. No promoter can apply for extension of registration of the project without updating all the QPRs of the preceding quarters.

news.title: Training and certification mandatory for registration of agents with UP-RERA
news.para: To begin with, UP-RERA is inviting online applications from the agents of Lucknow, Gautambudh Nagar, Kanpur, Gorakhpur, Varanasi, Prayagraj and Moradabad for enrollment in the training.
